Christopher P. Sloan (born September 28, 1954) is a science communicator, art director, author, and avocational paleontologist. Sloan is a four-time award-winning author of children’s books written for the National Geographic Society. He teaches modern approaches to science art online for the Academy of Art University in San Francisco, and is chairman of the Lanzendorf Paleo-Art Committee of the Society of Vertebrate Paleontology, an advisory board member of Exposé, a juried annual of computer graphic art. He is an active participant in the Smithsonian Institution National Museum of Natural History’s Human Origins Program and the National Evolutionary Synthesis Center. Most of Sloan’s time is concerned with being President of Science Visualization, a science media company he started in 2010. The firm is based in the Washington, D.C metropolitan area..
